\title{"security Ownership Map"}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Analyze git repositories to build a security ownership topology (people-to-file), compute bus factor and sensitive-code ownership, and export CSV/JSON for graph databases and visualization. Trigger only when the user explicitly wants a security-oriented ownership or bus-factor analysis grounded in git history (for example: orphaned sensitive code, security maintainers, CODEOWNERS reality checks for risk, sensitive hotspots, or ownership clusters). Do not trigger for general maintainer lists or non-security ownership questions."}

\subtree{
\title{Security Ownership Map}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Build a bipartite graph of people and files from git history, then compute ownership risk and export graph artifacts for Neo4j/Gephi. Also build a file co-change graph (Jaccard similarity on shared commits) to cluster files by how they move together while ignoring large, noisy commits.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Requirements}
\ul{
\li{Python 3}
\li{\code{\startverb networkx\stopverb} (required; community detection is enabled by default)}
}

\p{Install with:}

\pre{\startverb
pip install networkx
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow}
\ol{
\li{Scope the repo and time window (optional \code{\startverb --since/--until\stopverb}).}
\li{Decide sensitivity rules (use defaults or provide a CSV config).}
\li{Build the ownership map with \code{\startverb scripts/run_ownership_map.py\stopverb} (co-change graph is on by default; use \code{\startverb --cochange-max-files\stopverb} to ignore supernode commits).}
\li{Communities are computed by default; graphml output is optional (\code{\startverb --graphml\stopverb}).}
\li{Query the outputs with \code{\startverb scripts/query_ownership.py\stopverb} for bounded JSON slices.}
\li{Persist and visualize (see \code{\startverb references/neo4j-import.md\stopverb}).}
}

\p{By default, the co-change graph ignores common “glue” files (lockfiles, \code{\startverb .github/*\stopverb}, editor config) so clusters reflect actual code movement instead of shared infra edits. Override with \code{\startverb --cochange-exclude\stopverb} or \code{\startverb --no-default-cochange-excludes\stopverb}. Dependabot commits are excluded by default; override with \code{\startverb --no-default-author-excludes\stopverb} or add patterns via \code{\startverb --author-exclude-regex\stopverb}.}

\p{If you want to exclude Linux build glue like \code{\startverb Kbuild\stopverb} from co-change clustering, pass:}

\pre{\startverb
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/run_ownership_map.py \
  --repo /path/to/linux \
  --out ownership-map-out \
  --cochange-exclude "**/Kbuild"
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick start}
\p{Run from the repo root:}

\pre{\startverb
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/run_ownership_map.py \
  --repo . \
  --out ownership-map-out \
  --since "12 months ago" \
  --emit-commits
\stopverb}

\p{Defaults: author identity, author date, and merge commits excluded. Use \code{\startverb --identity committer\stopverb}, \code{\startverb --date-field committer\stopverb}, or \code{\startverb --include-merges\stopverb} if needed.}

\p{Example (override co-change excludes):}

\pre{\startverb
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/run_ownership_map.py \
  --repo . \
  --out ownership-map-out \
  --cochange-exclude "**/Cargo.lock" \
  --cochange-exclude "**/.github/**" \
  --no-default-cochange-excludes
\stopverb}

\p{Communities are computed by default. To disable:}

\pre{\startverb
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/run_ownership_map.py \
  --repo . \
  --out ownership-map-out \
  --no-communities
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Sensitivity rules}
\p{By default, the script flags common auth/crypto/secret paths. Override by providing a CSV file:}

\pre{\startverb
# pattern,tag,weight
**/auth/**,auth,1.0
**/crypto/**,crypto,1.0
**/*.pem,secrets,1.0
\stopverb}

\p{Use it with \code{\startverb --sensitive-config path/to/sensitive.csv\stopverb}.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Output artifacts}
\p{\code{\startverb ownership-map-out/\stopverb} contains:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb people.csv\stopverb} (nodes: people)}
\li{\code{\startverb files.csv\stopverb} (nodes: files)}
\li{\code{\startverb edges.csv\stopverb} (edges: touches)}
\li{\code{\startverb cochange_edges.csv\stopverb} (file-to-file co-change edges with Jaccard weight; omitted with \code{\startverb --no-cochange\stopverb})}
\li{\code{\startverb summary.json\stopverb} (security ownership findings)}
\li{\code{\startverb commits.jsonl\stopverb} (optional, if \code{\startverb --emit-commits\stopverb})}
\li{\code{\startverb communities.json\stopverb} (computed by default from co-change edges when available; includes \code{\startverb maintainers\stopverb} per community; disable with \code{\startverb --no-communities\stopverb})}
\li{\code{\startverb cochange.graph.json\stopverb} (NetworkX node-link JSON with \code{\startverb community_id\stopverb} + \code{\startverb community_maintainers\stopverb}; falls back to \code{\startverb ownership.graph.json\stopverb} if no co-change edges)}
\li{\code{\startverb ownership.graphml\stopverb} / \code{\startverb cochange.graphml\stopverb} (optional, if \code{\startverb --graphml\stopverb})}
}

\p{\code{\startverb people.csv\stopverb} includes timezone detection based on author commit offsets: \code{\startverb primary_tz_offset\stopverb}, \code{\startverb primary_tz_minutes\stopverb}, and \code{\startverb timezone_offsets\stopverb}.}
}

\subtree{
\title{LLM query helper}
\p{Use \code{\startverb scripts/query_ownership.py\stopverb} to return small, JSON-bounded slices without loading the full graph into context.}

\p{Examples:}

\pre{\startverb
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out people --limit 10
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out files --tag auth --bus-factor-max 1
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out person --person alice@corp --limit 10
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out file --file crypto/tls
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out cochange --file crypto/tls --limit 10
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out summary --section orphaned_sensitive_code
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out community --id 3
\stopverb}

\p{Use \code{\startverb --community-top-owners 5\stopverb} (default) to control how many maintainers are stored per community.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Basic security queries}
\p{Run these to answer common security ownership questions with bounded output:}

\pre{\startverb
# Orphaned sensitive code (stale + low bus factor)
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out summary --section orphaned_sensitive_code

# Hidden owners for sensitive tags
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out summary --section hidden_owners

# Sensitive hotspots with low bus factor
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out summary --section bus_factor_hotspots

# Auth/crypto files with bus factor <= 1
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out files --tag auth --bus-factor-max 1
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out files --tag crypto --bus-factor-max 1

# Who is touching sensitive code the most
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out people --sort sensitive_touches --limit 10

# Co-change neighbors (cluster hints for ownership drift)
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out cochange --file path/to/file --min-jaccard 0.05 --limit 20

# Community maintainers (for a cluster)
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/query_ownership.py --data-dir ownership-map-out community --id 3

# Monthly maintainers for the community containing a file
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/community_maintainers.py \
  --data-dir ownership-map-out \
  --file network/card.c \
  --since 2025-01-01 \
  --top 5

# Quarterly buckets instead of monthly
python skills/skills/security-ownership-map/scripts/community_maintainers.py \
  --data-dir ownership-map-out \
  --file network/card.c \
  --since 2025-01-01 \
  --bucket quarter \
  --top 5
\stopverb}

\p{Notes:}

\ul{
\li{Touches default to one authored commit (not per-file). Use \code{\startverb --touch-mode file\stopverb} to count per-file touches.}
\li{Use \code{\startverb --window-days 90\stopverb} or \code{\startverb --weight recency --half-life-days 180\stopverb} to smooth churn.}
\li{Filter bots with \code{\startverb --ignore-author-regex '(bot|dependabot)'\stopverb}.}
\li{Use \code{\startverb --min-share 0.1\stopverb} to show stable maintainers only.}
\li{Use \code{\startverb --bucket quarter\stopverb} for calendar quarter groupings.}
\li{Use \code{\startverb --identity committer\stopverb} or \code{\startverb --date-field committer\stopverb} to switch from author attribution.}
\li{Use \code{\startverb --include-merges\stopverb} to include merge commits (excluded by default).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Summary format (default)}
\p{Use this structure, add fields if needed:}

\pre{\startverb
{
  "orphaned_sensitive_code": [
    {
      "path": "crypto/tls/handshake.rs",
      "last_security_touch": "2023-03-12T18:10:04+00:00",
      "bus_factor": 1
    }
  ],
  "hidden_owners": [
    {
      "person": "alice@corp",
      "controls": "63% of auth code"
    }
  ]
}
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Graph persistence}
\p{Use \code{\startverb references/neo4j-import.md\stopverb} when you need to load the CSVs into Neo4j. It includes constraints, import Cypher, and visualization tips.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Notes}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb bus_factor_hotspots\stopverb} in \code{\startverb summary.json\stopverb} lists sensitive files with low bus factor; \code{\startverb orphaned_sensitive_code\stopverb} is the stale subset.}
\li{If \code{\startverb git log\stopverb} is too large, narrow with \code{\startverb --since\stopverb} or \code{\startverb --until\stopverb}.}
\li{Compare \code{\startverb summary.json\stopverb} against CODEOWNERS to highlight ownership drift.}
}
}
}